text: The image is a black and white movie poster for the film "Miss Ingird Bergman's Gowns Designed by Edith Head". The poster prominently features the film's title at the top, followed by the names of the film's musical director, c. bakaleinikoff, and the orchestral arrangements editor, gil grau. Below these names, the name of the sound designer, john e. tribby, is listed. Further down, the poster introduces the assistant director, william dorfman, and the cinematographer and editor, robert surtees. The film's release date is also mentioned on the poster. The background of the poster features a city skyline with tall buildings, suggesting an urban setting for the film. The text on the poster is clear and legible, indicating that it serves as an informative piece about the film's production team and details.
